Program: Discovery
Title: What remains to be discovered - the human brain
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jry9k
Last Broadcast Date: 15 January 2003
A series of programmes looking at the unanswered questions about the world around us. Programme two looks at something with which we are all very familiar, though few of us have ever seen. It is the most complex structure in the known universe: the human brain. But just how does it work?